<br>
I just last night got the chance to fool with this spell.  Since I got it, conditions haven't been good for rains (too high FR mobs, push problems or pet groups)<br>
<br>
Scirroco is amazing damage for the level you get it.  Even after factoring in a 25% resist rate and the mana used on malosini, I come up with around a 3.5 mana/damage ratio.  Far beyond anything else we have at that level, and without the problems that bolts run into in XP groups.<br>
<br>
<br>
Veddy, veddy nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=axxin>Axxin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:05:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8830.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Scirroco</span><hr size=1> Agreed.  I was on a raid in PoG last night, and used it extensively.  Even without Malosi (I was having MR issues) it was very efficient.  And on the two occasions where we got a double pull and I got all 4 waves to hit for full, it was like buttah. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2952<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:47:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8830.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Scirroco</span><hr size=1> There are numerous discussions of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sirocco</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and rain spells in general found in the:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells">Magician Spells Forum</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
